        "content": "<p>Is there a way to run simp on the whole local context at once? Instead of having to do<br>\n<code>simp at a,simp at b</code><br>\nbeing able to do something like<br>\n<code>simp at all</code></p>",
        "id": 229631920,
        "sender_full_name": "Guilherme Espada",
        "timestamp": 1615370939
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>simp at *</code> should work.</p>",
        "id": 229632342,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1615371128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In case it helps in other situations, <code>simp at a ⊢</code> applies simp at <code>a</code> and at the goal.  The symbol ⊢ is typed as <code>\\|-</code>.</p>",
        "id": 229632483,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1615371207
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks! very helpful!</p>",
        "id": 229632591,
        "sender_full_name": "Guilherme Espada",
        "timestamp": 1615371251
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can also type the goal symbol as <code>\\go</code> which might be easier <span aria-label=\"upside down\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f643\" role=\"img\" title=\"upside down\">:upside_down:</span></p>",
